A_372 - When we happen to suffer injuries, it can happen that if the injury is sufficiently serious (rape, broken bones), the body deforms elsewhere as a result of a sort of &ldquo;balancing&rdquo;. The opposite principle also applies: if overall health increases sufficiently, the person may improve their features significantly. In any case it is important to know however that breaking a crystal sculpture to fill a hole in the ground &ldquo;might&rdquo; not be a good idea...